FT  19 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Goldsmiths sales rise fails to materialise
The expected sales increase failed to materialise at Goldsmiths Group in the
back half of the year to February 29, and although there was some
improvement, the outcome for the year was a loss of Pounds 1.29m, against a
profit of Pounds 1.9m last time.
Sales were little changed at Pounds 40.6m (Pounds 41.5m).
Losses per share of 6.09p compared with earnings of 5.67p previously.
The proposed final dividend has been cut to 0.3p (1.5p), bringing the total
for the year to 1.8p (3p).
